junit.framework.Test
public class WebTestRunner
extends net.sourceforge.jwebunit.WebTestCase

Provides an adapter between the objects in this package and the assertions provided by jWebUnit. Has facilities for testing at the resource, form, or test case level.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Steven Handy
See Also:
WebSite, WebResource, WebForm, WebSession, XmlUtils

testForm

public void testForm(java.lang.String res,
                     java.lang.String frm)
Provides simplified interface to execute tests against a specific form found in the current web site. All test cases for the form will be executed. Invokes the private method testForm(WebForm, url) to run the test cases.

Parameters:
res - Name of the resource in which the form is located.
frm - Name of the form on which to run test cases.

testFormTestCase

public void testFormTestCase(java.lang.String res,
                             java.lang.String frm,
                             java.lang.String testCase)
Provides simplified interface to test a single test case for a form found in the current web site. Invokes the private method testFormTestCase(WebForm, Node) to run the test case.

Parameters:
res - Name of the resource in which the form is located.
frm - Name of the form on which to run the test case.
testCase - Name of the test case to be run.
